  "notes": "Karakalpak (Qaraqalpaqsha), Kipchak Turkic language of Karakalpakstan (Uzbekistan). The mapping above is the 2016 Latin alphabet, the current official script; a Cyrillic alphabet is also in use and is not modelled here — Latin input is assumed. Regular one-letter-one-phoneme orthography with front/back vowel harmony (⟨á ó ú i e⟩ front, ⟨a o u ı⟩ back). ISO 639-3 is kaa and Glottolog kara1467; the Wikidata row supplied for this code pointed at the Karakalpak Wiktionary project rather than the language item, so no QID is asserted here.",
